<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10019652084210></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10019652084210><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=88643&mid=10019652084210>A Squire?! Hmpf!</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=88643&mid=10019652084210#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=88643><span id= >Kaldolur</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 1st 3:40 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Although I'm dwarf, small in stature, I am proud of the fact that I have worked my way up through the ranks to become a 30th Paladin of Brell - untwinked, of course. Granted, level 30 is far from the pinnacle - but it is a worthy achievement none-the-less. Right?<br><br>You can imagine my chagrin then, as I stood before Marko in the Hall of Truth and inquired about the mystical sword, Soulfire.<br><br>"Art thou a squire?" He asked with no expression upon his face.<br><br>Squire?! Surely I had misunderstood him. Of course he hadn't had ample opportunity to recognize that it was me, Kaldolur Britebeard: slayer of thousands (well, most certainly hundreds) of orcs, defiler of DVinn! Why I personally have wandered the feces-strewn halls of Blackburrow, slaughtering gnoll commanders and elite by numbers untold! The fire goblins of Solusek have learned to tremble at the mere mention of my name! I wield the mighty sword Ghoulbane!! How dare he?!<br><br>But... if I fail to respond in proper manner, I will never receive the quest for the second Holy Sword. I swallowed hard and bit my lip...<br><br>"I..." Blast. "I am a s-squire." I murmured in a quite tone.<br><br>And just like that, Marko was off like a shot, explaining the steps I needed to take to prove myself worthy to the Paladins of the Hall of Truth. He had no idea the hell he had just put me through. He was also (apparently) unfazed at the monumental revelation I had just made. Hmpf! Oh well, what do you expect from a guy who hangs around the garden all day, just waiting for eager young adventurers to come do his dirty work for him?<br><br>Although the incident hadn't impacted Marko at all, it certainly made an impression upon me. And I learned a valuable lesson. No matter how experienced we become, no matter how many adventures we've got "under our belts", no matter how many seasons we live through - there is always still more. The important thing is, that we learn during those times, and always seek to improve ourselves - not in the eyes of others, but in our own eyes.<br><br>I've traveled across the Commonlands since that day, bought drinks for an old man at the Seafarer's Roost on the Freeport Docks, and even spent time with a babbling, deranged prisoner in the dungeons beneath the Freeport Arena. And with each adventure, as each day dawns anew - I ask myself one simple question: "How can I become a better person today?".<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kaldolur Britebeard<br>Dwarven Paladin of the 50th season<br>Vazaelle</td></tr>
